<b><h1> S I K E!!!!

out of every kid i've known, you were the last person i thought that i would be writting this about. 



you are still my brother forever and then some, but it's gonna be hard to look at you the same and think that something like this wouldnt happen again, what's next vegan too?



so with this marks the first kid dropping from 24, i guess its something that is kinda inevitable with a crew gettin bigger, but you always hope your crew never expriences it. especially when its one of the kids who starts it.


for everything you claimed to love, all this meant nothing.. all the times you said you'd never break meant nothing, all the times you laughed with me at the kids who were edge and then talked shit about it meant nothing.

as much as i love you.. you are just the same as the last kid who was all big about it and then dropped.




i love you to death, but forever was a lot shorter than i thought...




andrew 24 r.i.p

HAPPY BIRTHDAY
i just saw The Butterfly Effect, it was pretty awesome. a movie that actually had a pretty innovative idea for once.

The show tonight was actually a lot of fun. With Honor was amazing. saw a fuckin ton of new kids, i just hope they stick around, and arnt just at the big shows.

going to work for danny northside again tomorrow, good time as always. that and im getting tattooed.

ohh, the roadie for sworn enemy almost knocked my teeth out... which would have been really, really, really lame.

so i have been feeling better about stuff lately.


i need to get this band started with everyone, it pretty much a priority on my list.
whoo got their charges dropped. AND WHAT!
create your own visited states map or write about it on the open travel guide midwest is a mutha fucka

im gettin back into art really heavily, that is something i am way excited about.. hopefully i can start something up wher i am selling my artwork. that would be amazing.

to be gettin paid for doing something i love, is all i am about.
first blood was awesome. im tired.

so i get to see first blood tomorrow night, im fuckin stoked. 

and tonight i get to see shai hulud, with chad singing..shits gonna get crunk.




on another note.

martine and i are starting a band..SKULLDOZER, we are only gonna tour japan.

i called my dad at 3:30am his time to tell him, how much i missed him. and how much i love him.


he said it was the best thing i have ever given him.

i cant wait to see him on my birthday.

Jaxon is lookin for pictures of any Unbreakable set, so if you got em let me know, or let him know.

thanx!

last night was embrace today, it was a whole lot of fun. 

got to hang out with all the boston kids.

watched o hagen play in short shorts which is always positive =]

i kicked jaesyn in the face while he was singing, hahahaha, but i love jaesyn so its all good.

so i just got done tattooing for literally 8 hours, and that entire time, i was totally happy.


all the tattoos i did tonight turned out way better than i expected,  i figured i would be a little rusty, but i pretty jumped into right where i left off.


all in all tonight has been the best night in a while.


im saving up to buy a power supply, and im starting up as soon as i possibly can.
im about to tattoo again for the first time in a while. im fuckin stoked, i miss it so much. hopefully this will get me back on my track

today was one of those days where it just felt good to hang out by myself. i tried to think about stuff. tried to figure out what path in life i'm gonna take.


then i realized.... i got my whole life to figure out where i am gonna be in 5 years. i might as well just work on the whole day to day thing.
today is a lazy dog dangling afternoon, my arm is wicked sore.

I got tattooed for 5 hours today, it looks rad, but i am sooo fuckin sore and tired.

its sleepy time faggots.


OH and i hope all the boys in Army Trip 2k4 have a blast and dance all the cali kids stupid.
So......Prayer For Cleansing is playing in North Carolina on march 14th....im going no matter what it fuckin takes.

everyone definetly missed a really great band in tucson tonight. Tomora, prolly one of the most intellegent bands i have heard in a long time.


make sure you hit up their show in phx on the 17th

Happy New Year.

me lil Tim and Nate, just jumped off of our porch roof into our hypothermia pool, and took a shower.


thats how we fuckin do.

highlights of 2003:

-starting a band

-getting a job at AOL.....and quiting it heh

-playing our first show as UNBREAKABLE(you FAGGOTS)

-playing with bands like, figure four, comeback kid, judas cradle, most precious blood, the hoods, integrity, out to win, will to live, folsom, die young, bound in blood, scars of tomorrow, beneath the ahes, ect.

-releasing a demo

-sellin out of every t-shirt design we ever made (mainly in part to drew's excellent marketing skills)

-going on tour and playing, vegas, san antoinio, laredo, houston.

-makin tons of new friends

-playing axtionfest.....finally 

-gettin over my fear of flying

-buyin a car im a finally proud of

-overcoming a lot of problems.

-moving to phx.

-playin a great final show....both times

-makin it to 2004
